The paper discusses a method for efficient high dimensional blue noise sampling, which is a common problem in computational geometry (cs.CG) and graphics (cs.GR). The method involves optimization (cs.DS) and can be applied to motion planning (cs.SY) as well. Additionally, the paper mentions applications in meshing, which could fall under numerical analysis (cs.NA).
